@endnode
@node "HowToInstall" "How to install MMKeyboard"

@{MS "How to install MMKeyboard"}

Just use the include installer script to install this application!@{par}

@{b}Don't try to install this archive by hand, because this may cause many trouble. The automatic installation
ensures a minimum use of disc and memory space!@{ub}

@endnode
@node "Quickstart" "How to get it work?"

@{MS "How to get it work?"}

After the @{"installation" link "HowToInstall"} reboot and open the preferences program
(MMKeyboard).@{par}

@{MS "Set-up the keyboard"}

First you need to select a keyboard. Press the keyboard setup gadget at the top of the window to
open the keyboard selection. Try to find your keyboard and close the window by hitting the use
gadget.@{PAR}

If your keyboard is not available then use the menu to open the @{"keyboard editor" link "KeEd"}.@{PAR}

The keyboard editor is very easy to use:@{PAR}

1. Press the multimedia key you want to add. A hex string (eg. $80000E032) appears in the Key List.@{PAR}
2. A string input field with the same hex string gets active. Try to select the name by using the
popup gadget behind or enter the name by using the input box.@{PAR}
3. If there are more multimedia keys to add then proceed with 1.@{PAR}
4. Select an existing vendor (eg. Logitech) with the popup gadget or enter a new vendor.
Then enter the new keyboard name.@{PAR}
5. Use the @{"save gadget" link "KeEdKeSa"} to save the keyboard settings.@{PAR}
6. Send me your configuration to include it into my archive. (-8@{PAR}

After saving the keyboard settings close the keyboard editor. Now select the keyboard you just created and proceed by
pressing the use button.@{PAR}

@{MS "Setup the desired hotkeys"}

Back in the "MMKeyboard - Main Setup" window we want to setup our first hotkey to start AWeb with the WWW key. Any other
key is doing the job, too! It's just an example.@{PAR}

1. Select "New..." and the "Hotkey Set-Up" window is opening.@{PAR}
2. Enter a hotkey name like "AWeb" or "starting AWeb".@{PAR}
3. Press the popup gadget behind the hotkey gadget and a new hotkey window is opening. Now it's time
to press the WWW key with or without qualifier. If the hotkey is correct push the ok button to
continue.@{PAR}
4. Now it's time to select an action. Choose CLI as exec type.@{PAR}
5. Use the popup gadget behind the "command" gadget to select the AWeb program file.@{PAR}
6. Press the "use" gadget to store the hotkey.@{PAR}
7. Proceed with 1. if there are any additional hotkeys to add.@{PAR}
8. Back in the main window select save.@{PAR}
9. Now it's time to test the hotkey. Press the hotkey combination you defined within section 2.@{PAR}

@endnode
@node "History" "History"

@{MS "History"}

This text is telling the story of MMKeyboard like a diary.

 @{MC "V0.35"}

First version.

 @{MC "V0.36"}

FEATURE: Separated commodity and preferences program.@{par}
FEATURE: Now it's possible to swap the Win and Alt keys to place
the Amiga keys next to the space key like on original Amiga keyboard.@{par}
FEATURE: Small keyboard configuration menu!@{par}
FEATURE: The mouse is blocked during password session.@{par}
FEATURE: Now its possible to create a personal password requester

 @{MC "V0.36 - V0.62"}

CHANGED: Many changes (file structure, directory, icons, GUI).@{par}
CHANGED: Installer Script.@{par}
CHANGED: Many small changes on the PIC software.@{par}
FEATURE: Some password GUIs included. (Thanks to Timo Hegemann)@{par}
FEATURE: It's possible to deactivate The @{"password GUI" link "PassGUIP"}.@{par}
FEATURE: Now it's possible to display the password GUI on a @{"separate screen" link "PassScre"}.@{par}
FEATURE: The keyboard is now full reset-handler compatible!@{par}
FEATURE: It's possible to connect @{"optional LEDs" link "FAQSTune"}

 @{MC "V0.63"}

FEATURE: PowerUp/PowerDown by using the keyboard!

 @{MC "V0.64"}

BUGFIX: Fixed EnforcerHit caused by MMKeyboardPrefs!@{par}
FEATURE: A new @{"PIC set-up" link "PICC"} allows to easy config the PIC!

 @{MC "V1.00"}

First non beta aminet release!

 @{MC "V1.01"}

BUGFIX: Small PIC change! (no update required)

 @{MC "V1.02"}

CHANGED: Many manual changes.

 @{MC "V1.03"}

FEATURE: The @{"main window" link "MAST"} is now sizeable!

 @{MC "V1.04"}

FEATURE: The @{"keyboard set-up" link "KeEd"} is now sizeable.

 @{MC "V1.05"}

FEATURE: Second power line signal for direct use with ATX-power supply.

 @{MC "V1.06"}

BUGFIX: Many internal enhancements! (password request)

 @{MC "V1.07"}

BUGFIX: Removed small error within the Amiga resync code. This bug caused a repeated "^" after
sync lost!

 @{MC "V1.08"}

BUGFIX: I forgot to predefine the MenuPop key! (Thanks to Jeff Pierce)

 @{MC "V1.09"}

CHANGED: Documentation update!

 @{MC "V1.10"}

BUGFIX: Added a small workaround for the "missing password picture" problem! It seems that it's a
ILBM/picture datatype problem, because sometimes the DTA_Sync message is missing.

 @{MC "V1.11"}

CHANGED: Small PIC change! There is no update needed! By using the new hex file the password hotkey
is "scroll lock"! It more logic now! The scroll lock light is used for password indication and the
key is activating the password. F11 can be used as free hotkey!
BUGFIX: The password screen is now opening with the default font when the specified isn't available.
(reported by Klaus von der Haar)@{par}
INFO: The "Missing password picture" problem isn't gone! The problem is the
ILBM Datatype which isn't displaying the picture at all, even when refreshing it via
brute force method. If this is happening on your system then use a different file format! The RGFX
or PNG seem to be a good choice!

 @{MC "V1.12"}

CHANGED: Reworked the "Enter Hotkey" window. The previous version was only a big hack.@{par}
BUGFIX: Fixed the trash file problem when quitting MMKeyboard prefs.@{par}
BUGFIX: No more hardware problems! The PIC is now auto resetting itself!

 @{MC "V1.13"}

BUGFIX: Small fix for the password mode, that may be caused by some hardware versions! (depends on
the R/C tolerance)

 @{MC "V1.14"}

BUGFIX: The keyboard repeat wasn't filtered correct! (Reported by Thomas Wenzel)@{par}
FEATURE: Optional @{"Reset Switch" link "/Pictures/Optional.ilbm/MAIN"}@{par}
BUGFIX: Fixed GUI barlabel spacing.

 @{MC "V1.15"}

CHANGED: Manual changes.@{par}
FEATURE: Added a @{"picture" link "/Pictures/MMK_Mersmann1.jpg/main"} of my interface.

 @{MC "V1.16"}

CHANGED: Manual changes.@{par}
FEATURE: Now it's impossible to use F12 as power key, because this is blocking the PIC set-up.
(Reported by Michael Göcken)@{par}
BUGFIX: Normal hotkeys like "control alt f4" didn't work! Nobody noticed this bug before. In my case
I forgot to remove ToolManager, so it looked good until I removed this tool.@{par}
FEATURE: After loosing power the interface is using the last system power state.
FEATURE: Now it's possible to change the PIC set-up by using MMkeyboardPrefs. This feature requires
a PIC software version 1.16 or better.

 @{MC "V1.17"}

BUGFIX: The pretyped character in password window is now gone.@{par}
FEATURE: Now nearly 256 additional MM-keys are supported.

 @{MC "V1.18"}

FEATURE: An optional @{"switch" link "/Pictures/Optional.ilbm/MAIN"} allows to shut down and power
up your system. This feature requires a PIC software version 1.18 or better.@{par}
FEATURE: New "pseudo" hotkey! "KBPlug" allows to execute a program when the keyboard is plugged in.
This feature requires a PIC software version 1.18 or better.@{par}
FEATURE: New "pseudo" hotkey! "KBRESET" allows to execute commands right before the system
@{"resets" link "FAQSResetHandler"}.

 @{MC "V1.19"}

BUGFIX: Fixed window sizing bug within the @{"keyboard editor" link "KeEd"}.@{par}
CHANGED: Reworked the @{"main window" link "MAST"} and added a new @{"password set-up" link "Pass"}.@{par}
CHANGED: Many catalog changes.@{par}
BUGFIX: Closed password pack door. (Don't ask!) (PIC software version 1.19 or better required).@{par} @{par}
CHANGED: Manual changes.@{par}
FEATURE: Added new password gui.@{par}
FEATURE: Now it's possible to set-up the password gui with MMKeyboardPrefs.@{par}
FEATURE: New Password gui screenmode selector.@{par}
FEATURE: Now it's possible to test the password gui by using MMKeyboardPrefs.@{par}
FEATURE: @{"Right control key" link "PICCRCTR"} may be used as MultiMedia key, too. (PIC software version 1.19 or better required)@{par}
BUGFIX: The pressed hotkey wasn't removed correctly from the key stream. This caused unwanted input
in the active window.@{par}
FEATURE: @{"New execute type" link "EditExTy"}: @{"Macros" link "EditComm"}.

 @{MC "V1.20"}

FEATURE: New @{"schematic for 1200" link "/Pictures/A1200Connector.ilbm/MAIN"} included. Thanks to Olivier Croquette for the
information.@{par}
FEATURE: Keymaps for win keyboards included.@{par}
FEATURE: Preset for Highscreen MCK-800 keyboard included. Thanks to Norman Thiel!@{par}
BUGFIX: The command gadget in the hotkey set-up wasn't working correct when used in key command mode.
(reported by Norman Thiel)@{par}
FEATURE: Now it's possible to select the @{"Macro commands" link "EditComm"} by using a popup window!

 @{MC "V1.21"}

FEATURE: Preset for "Trust Ergo_Track", "Logitech Internet Navigator" and "TurboMedia" keyboards
included. Thanks to Nick Clover!

 @{MC "V1.22"}

BUGFIX: Removed some small bugs that never caused trouble.@{par}
CHANGED: Small optimisations to the gadget layout code.@{par}
FEATURE: Added a special @{"Amithlon" link "FAQSAmithlon"} version! Currently it's not clear how the
MMKey support will be implemented. This version requires a hardware emulation of the key transfer
protocol. With current versions of Amithlon MMKeyboard is only able to use normal keys. The hardware
and password configuration isn't required for Amithlon, so I removed it. Currently only
"Insert", "Page_Up", "Page_Down" and "F11" are working.

 @{MC "V1.23"}

FEATURE: The @{"key command" link "EditComm"} is now able to pass through user qualifiers.@{par}
FEATURE: A new bonus drawer is containing useful tools for MMKeyboard.

 @{MC "V1.24"}

FEATURE: Now it's possible to insert keyboard settings.@{par}
FEATURE: Added presets for the normal and the @{"Amithlon" link "FAQSAmithlon"} version.

 @{MC "V1.25"}

CHANGED: Optimised the keyboard handler to minimise CPU usage.@{par}
FEATURE: Now it's possible to specify a "UPSTROKE" qualifier for each key. By default MMKeyboard is
using the key down code for execution, but for some reason it may be useful to act only on key up to
avoid the input device auto repeat.

 @{MC "V1.26"}

FEATURE: The preferences windows are now using a modified version of the commodity input handler.
This allowed to disable all defined hotkey when the set-up window is open.@{par}
FEATURE: Now it's possible to select a defined hotkey by using it. E.g. you defined "CONTROL LSHIFT
F4" as hotkey, you can select the entry by using this combination.

 @{MC "V1.27"}

FEATURE: 8 new possible hotkeys for all keyboards. Well, these aren't very useful, but the
implementation isn't using any additional code or CPU usage with in the commodity. You can use the
Qualifier as keys. E.g. "CONTROL KRSHIFT" will start a tool by pressing control and the right shift
key. By adding a "K" in front of the qualifier it's handled as a real key. Please note that a
"-qualifier" of the key value is appearing. This is normal, because pressing  "lshift" is causing a
"lshift klshift". This is useful to install a keyboard reset on A1200 without a reset logic. Just
define "control lcommand krcommand" and start the reboot command.

 @{MC "V1.28"}

FEATURE: Shortcuts! Yes! The preferences supporting qualifier shortcuts. "CONTROL LALT RCOMMAND F10"
can be entered as "ct la lc f10". If available I used the first chars of the words: "CAPSLOCK" =
"CL". The "K" and "-" qualifier are working in the same way: "KCAPSLOCK" = "KCL". BTW: The input
isn't case sensitiv at all.

 @{MC "V1.29"}

BUGFIX: Fixed the macro WindowFlip (Now named "WindowNext"), to detect non depth windows. (reported by Boris
Ivic)@{par}
FEATURE: Added a new @{"Macros" link "Macros"} named @{"WindowPrev" link "MacrosWindowPrev"}, which is operating like
@{"WindowNext" link "MacrosWindowNext"} (was named "WindowFlip" in previous versions)

 @{MC "V1.30"}

BUGFIX: Found a bunch of bugs that never caused real trouble.@{par}
FEATURE: New macros

 @{MC "V1.31"}

FEATURE: Many small GUI enhancements.@{par}
BUGFIX: (Standard version only) The disabled capslock key was displayed as "capslock" which
interfeared with the "capslock" qualifier. Now the MMKey "CapsLock" is names "Shiftlock" to avoid
this problem.

 @{MC "V2.00"}

FEATURE: New archive/drawer/installation layout. Everything changed a little bit! It's strongly
required to use the included installation stuff to get a proper and working update.

 @{MC "V2.01-V2.09"}

CHANGED: Optimised the preferences and data file handling.

 @{MC "V2.10"}

BUGFIX: The key table within the keyboard can be switched. If the keyboard is using a different
key table by default, MMKeyboard was unable to work correct. Now the PIC turns tells keyboard to use
the right key table. There is no need to update the PIC! There'll be no difference for already
working keyboards. (gemeldet von Harald Frank)

 @{MC "V2.11"}

FEATURE: The stupid and a little hidden keyboard selector is gone. Now we have a real good looking
@{"keyboard selection" link "KeCh"} window. The old window is also available as separate
@{"keyboard editor" link "KeEd"}.@{par}
FEATURE: EjectTool V1.6 included!

 @{MC "V2.12"}

BUGFIX: The list handling routines never released memory to the system.

 @{MC "V2.13"}

CHANGED: Massive internal changes. These changes were required for the Amithlon implementation.
The Amithlon version now supports the new KeyID system.@{par}
CHANGED: Keyboard and Hotkey settings changed. Backward compatible loader is included.

 @{MC "V2.14"}

CHANGED: The name enter window is gone. When you're pressing the @{"new..." link "MASTNEWI"} button
in the @{"main window" link "MAST"} the @{"Meridian Set-up" link "Edit"} is opening
immediatly.@{par}
CHANGED: Many documentation changes.

 @{MC "V2.15"}

FEATURE: Added MMKeyboard-Logo during installation! (Thanks to Carsten Berger)@{par}
BUGFIX: The input handler type field was invalid.

 @{MC "V2.16"}

FEATURE: New @{"Macros" link "Macros"} @{"ScreenNext" link "MacrosScreenNext"} and
@{"ScreenPrev" link "MacrosScreenPrev"}.@{par}
FEATURE: Now it's possible to define @{"task" link "EditTask"} specific hotkeys. This allows
to use the same key within several applications and with different actions in the result.@{par}
BUGFIX: An unknown key was always converted into a $0000, which was converted back into a "^". It
seems this bug slipped though during V1.13.

 @{MC "V2.17"}

BUGFIX: Fixed a small bug within the Task stuff that broke the memory list. It never appeared with
MMKeyboard, but it did in Meridian, so it's fixed here, too. That's the good thing of "stealing" stuff
from other tools. (-8@{par}
FEATURE: New @{"Macros" link "Macros"}: @{"WindowToFront" link "MacrosWindowToFront"}  and
@{"WindowToBack" link "MacrosWindowToBack"}.

 @{MC "V2.18"}

CHANGED: Reworked the whole key setting stuff. Now we have a proper, fast and less memory consuming
key storage. No preferences converter this time, because the changes are to heavy. Sorry for that,
but it was required for implementation of new features. Just think about it: Until now MMKeyboard
used 7 different preferences formats. I don't want to waste any time to create a converter for all
this old stuff again. After this cleanup we have enough space for new features.@{par}
FEATURE: Thanks to the simplification it was possible to implement a more useful hotkey list.@{par}
CHANGED: Reworked the whole edit window to fix a few problems. Now the whole gadget stuff is faster
and smaller.@{par}
FEATURE: Thanks to the new settings it's possible to implement new macros with arguments.
ideas are welcome.@{par}
FEATURE: New @{"copy" link "MASTCOPY"} gadget allows to copy entries.@{par}
FEATURE: @{b}Full@{ub} Amithlon MMKey support.@{par}
BUGFIX: The keyboard setup menu opened the wrong window.@{par}
BUGFIX: The @{"copy..." link "MASTCOPY"}, @{"edit..." link "MASTEDIT"} and
@{"Remove..." link "MASTDELE"} gadgets are now visualy disabled, too@{par}
BUGFIX: Fixed the installer script! Pretend mode didn't work, because a destination file was used
as source.@{par}
BUGFIX: When leaving the @{"keyboard editor" link "KeEd"} the @{"keyboard set-up list" link "KeCh"}
will be updated.@{par}
FEATURE: New @{"Macros" link "Macros"}: @{"IEvent" link "MacrosIEvent"}.@{par}
UPDATE: New GUI-engine version used.

 @{MC "V2.19"}

CHANGED: @{"IEvent" link "MacrosIEvent"} is now more flexible to future extensions.@{par}
BUGFIX: No longer damaged stealth code messages. MMKeyboard is detecting foreign keys within the
keystream and finaly gets the original multimedia key again. A side effect is that the foreign keys
are passed though, so everything should work fine.@{par}
BUGFIX: Fixed task selection hotkey within the @{"Hotkey Set-up" link "Edit"} (reported by Boris
Ivic)@{par}
BUGFIX: The password GUI is working again!@{par}
BUGFIX: Very fast @{"keycodes" link "FAQSRAW"} aren't forgotten or mixed anymore. (Thanks to Karl Dietrich Bamler)@{par}
FEATURE: Added path through value for the @{"ievent command" link "MacrosIEvent"}. (requested by Karl Dietrich Bamler)@{par}
BUGFIX: Due a bug within the KeyComp utility the old keymaps caused illegal memory access. I used
another tool for keymap converting and now the enforcer problems are gone.@{par}
BUGFIX: The old hotkey handling stuff allowed to disorder the key action and very fast repeated keycodes caused that
the task option was ignored somehow.

 @{MC "V2.20"}

BUGFIX: Fixed Amithlon mmkey detecting bug! (reported by Harald Frank)@{par}
BUGFIX: Fixed the old "unable to open ''" bug! (reported by nearly anyone)@{par}
FEATURE: Improved keymap editor functions. Now it's possible to select the vendor and the key name
within a list. (requested by Harald Frank)@{par}
FEATURE: New gadgets within the main window: Up, Down,
Sort (requested by Martin Steigerwald)@{par}
BUGFIX: Some MMKeys caused the additional qualifier "NUMERICPAD". (reported by Martin Steigerwald)@{par}
FEATURE: Added external commands for flexible enhancement.(requested by Harald Frank)@{par}
BUGFIX: There was a small change that the macros @{"WindowNext" link "MacrosWindowNext"}
and @{"WindowPrev" link "MacrosWindowPrev"} could crash when call very fast on very fast systems.@{par}
BUGFIX: Position and size of the listview windows will be saved, too.

 @{MC "V2.21"}

BUGFIX: Fixed MuForce Hit within the MMKeyboard preferences.

 @{MC "V2.22"}

UPDATE: Reworked the hotkey string generation stuff. Now the alias is working here, too.@{par}
CHANGED: Many changes to the manual. (Thanks to Dietmar Knoll)@{par}
CHANGED: No more external "real" commands! All commands are listed within one list. That's much
easier to use and the program gets shorter.@{par}
FEATURE: New @{"macros" link "Macros"}: @{"WindowMove" link "MacrosWindowMove"},
@{"MouseMove" link "MacrosMouseMove"} and @{"MouseClick" link "MacrosMouseClick"}.

 @{MC "V2.23 - V3.11"}

CHANGED: Rewrote the commodity and the preferences utility from scratch.@{par}
CHANGED: MMKeyboard is now using a MUI User interface.@{par}
FEATURE: Added many new macros. Also included the EjectTool Command.@{par}
BUGFIX: Fixed bug within the settings notify. (reported by @{b}Ingo Schmitz@{ub})
CHANGED: Worked around the MorphOS 1.4.x input.device bug. AddEvent().
CHANGED: MMKeyboard and Meridian are now fully sharing their source codes.@{par}
FEATURE: The MMKeyboard list now contains additional information on the hotkeys
in the list.@{par}
BUGFIX: Under rare circumstances the catalog wasn't accepted and English was used as
fallback.@{par}
CHANGED: Changed and adapted to the latest CLIB. Many routines were removed from the sources.@{par}
CHANGED: Many small changes within the catalogs. Also used the new features of the new SimpleCat
tool.@{par}
BUGFIX: The PopUp-key wasn't checked correct! (reported by Ingo Schmitz).@{par}
BUGFIX: Fixed a Problem within the GUI Engine. Now it's possible to configure
the MUI gui without locking the preferences.@{par}
BUGFIX: Some gadgets weren't in the cycle chain.@{par}
CHANGED: Tons of changes and fixes within the documentation.@{par}
FEATURE: Added "NoToFront" option to the @{"macros" link "Macros"}
@{"WindowNext" link "MacrosWindowNext"} and
@{"WindowPrev" link "MacrosWindowPrev"}. These allow to browse though
the windows without having the window beeing pushed to front.@{par}
WORKAROUND: Worked around the missing WindowClose input class in MorphOS. Now the macro
@{"WindowClose" link "MacrosWindowClose"} should work with MorphOS, too.@{par}
BUGFIX: Used new PPC smallstart.o to avoid wbstart enforcer hits. (Reported by
@{b}Pawel Stefanski@{ub})@{par}
FEATURE: Added command type arexx. (Requested by @{b}Pawel Stefanski@{ub}) and many other!@{par}
FEATURE: New macro arguments for @{"WindowNext" link "MacrosWindowNext"} and
@{"WindowPrev" link "MacrosWindowPrev"}.

 @{MC "V3.12"}

CHANGED: Reworked source to support the SDI_#?.h includes made by @{b}Jens
Langner@{ub} and @{b}Dirk Stöcker@{ub}! Thanks for the stuff guys!@{par}
CHANGED: Added missing "no menu" tag for windows without menu. :)@{par}
UPDATE: Set the morphos timeout to the future again. Since nobody noticed that
there is a timeout, I guess noone is using it with MorphOS 1.4 or all clocks
are going wrong.

 @{MC "V3.13"}

FEATURE: Bubble help to the entire application. Took me 4 hours to copy all the
strings from the manuals into the catalogs, but it was worth it.@{par}
CHANGED: Massive changes to the documentation.@{par}
CHANGED: Recompiled with the latest compiler lib version which fixes many small
gui and device glitches.

 @{MC "V3.14"}

FEATURE: WinUAE version included.@{par}
FEATURE: Three new macros: @{"Cut" link "MacrosCut"}, @{"Copy" link "MacrosCopy"} and
@{"Paste" link "MacrosPaste"}. (requested by @{b}Bernd Roesch@{ub})@{par}
FEATURE: Added three additional macros: @{"ReqOk" link "MacrosReqOk"},
@{"ReqCancel" link "MacrosReqCancel"} and @{"WBToFront" link "MacrosWBToFront"}.@{par}
BUGFIX: Removed very bad enforcer hit during config data load. (reported by
@{b}Bernd Roesch@{ub})

 @{MC "V3.15"}

BUGFIX: Paste macro used the wrong key.@{par}
FEATURE: Added DirectX compliant keyboard setup which should handle all modern keyboards.@{par}
FEATURE: New macro @{"IRComSend" link "MacrosIRComSend"}.@{par}
BUGFIX: Numpad keys were converted wrong by the preferences editor.@{par}
BUGFIX: The upstroke qualifier was converted wrong by the preferences editor.(reported by
@{b}Bernd Roesch@{ub})
BUGFIX: Fixed several bubble strings, which caused freezing.@{par}
CHANGED: Many small changes for upcoming AMC and IRComRemote.

 @{MC "V3.16"}

BUGFIX: Fixed possible enforcer hit or crash when starting preferences twice.@{par}
FEATURE: Amithlon - it's now possible to disable Keypatches. (requested by Timo Hegemann)@{par}
FEATURE: Amithlon - LALT and RALT can be remapped by RControl, MenuPop and Insert. (requested by Timo Hegemann)

 @{MC "V3.17"}

BUGFIX: When using MorphOS 1.5 the key code 0xe036 was handled wrong.@{par}
CHANGED: Changed direct hotkey input of the editor window. Now it's limited to
multimedia keys again, because there were conflicts with standard clipboard and
string input hotkeys, which caused unwanted changes to the hotkey field.@{par}
UPDATE: Updated task filter.

 @{MC "V3.18"}

BUGFIX: Fixed "upstroke" handling for Morphos.@{par}
BUGFIX: "upstroke" in hot key input got filtered under special circumstances. (reported
by Thomas Igracki)@{par}
CHANGED: Recompiled with latest headers and clibs.

 @{MC "V3.19"}

CHANGED: Predefined settings had alt<>amiga swap enabled. (Reported by Nick Clover and Ferrán Garcia)@{par}
FEATURE: New AmigaOS4 PPC version included. (Many thanks to Nick Clover, Ferrán
Garcia and Matthew Treasure for testing)

 @{MC "V3.20"}

BUGFIX: Fixed "+" and "-" qualifier handling, so Qualifiers can be used as hotkey again.@{par}
CHANGED: Updated outdated hotkey section which still used the very old "k"
version of the now named "+" feature. Also fixed a wrong example.@{par}
FEATURE: Enabled additional OS4 mouse buttons.@{par}
BUGFIX: OS4 version didn't filter the hotkey from input stream. (Many thanks to
Nick Clover)

 @{MC "V3.21"}

BUGFIX: The AOS68K version didn't work correct since implementing the UAE
version. (Reported by Wolfgang Hosemann)

