@node "Hardware" "The Interface Hardware"

@{MS "The Interface Hardware"}

@{b}The hardware is not required when using Amithlon, AmithlonXL or MorphOS!@{ub}@{par}

@{b}If you're not able or want to create the interface yourself, then it's possible to
@{"buy" link "FAQSHardBuy"}@{ub}@{par}

The @{"interface" link "/Pictures/Hardware.ilbm/MAIN"} is very easy! If you already build the
IBMKey Hardware delivered by the EPic Archive, then just update the @{"PIC" link "FAQSPIC"}.@{par}

Here are some optional @{"features" link "/Pictures/Optional.ilbm/MAIN"} for the hardware and
a @{"schematic" link "/Pictures/A1200Connector.ilbm/Main"} for the A1200.@{par}

Depending on your Amiga and your keyboard other connectors are used, that's the reason the schematic
is universal. Because of the size it's not very easy to solder PS/2 Plugs, so I recommend to cut an
extender cable.@{par}

Here is a @{"picture" link "/Pictures/MMK_Mersmann1.jpg/main"} of my interface. The PIC @{"fits exact" link "/Pictures/MMK_Mersmann2.jpg/main"} into
a 9 to 9 sub-d interface box. The box endings are filled with small plastic piece's cut from a
standard disc.@{par}

You shouldn't make the wires to long! Just use 10cm or less on each side should be enough. You're
able to use an extender if required!@{par}

The circuit itself can be done on a simple PCB tracks or completely without! Just make sure there
aren't any shortcuts. It's possible to create an interface that isn't much bigger than the PIC
itself.@{par}

Please also read the information about the @{"PIC" link "FAQSPIC"}!@{par}

If there are any problems then read the @{"FAQ" link "FAQS"} section for further information!@{par}

@{code}
@{"Predefined" link "PICC"} special keys:

  Key          Amiga result
----------------------------
Home         Shift Cursor Left
End          Shift Cursor Right
Page_Up      Shift Cursor Up
Page_Down    Shift Cursor Down
PopUp        Left Amiga m (Screen flip)
PrintScr     Right Amiga p
Break        Control c
Insert       Help
F11          MultiMedia Extension Hotkey
F12          MultiMedia Extension Hotkey
ScrLock      MultiMedia Extension Hotkey
Left Win     Left Amiga
Right Win    Right Amiga

@endnode
