----|--------|--------|--------|---------|--------|--------|--------|--------|

@endnode
@node "FAQSResetHandler" "What is a 'Reset Handler' doing?"
@toc "FAQS"

@{MS "What is a 'Reset Handler' doing?"}

The reset handler in the most cases is used to do cleanup stuff right before the system resets. This
feature is used only by a few tools and file systems, but it is very useful.@{par}

Just think about a file system using a write cache. The handler allows to store
the cache on HD before system reset. A text editor may backup a text just in
case the user forgot to save. I am using the reset handler to eject my ZIP disc,
because there shouldn't be a disc in the drive on power off.@{par}

The reason that this handler is used rarely is that it's normally only working
on A2000, A3000 and A4000. Even some A2000 and A3000 keyboards don't support the
reset handler stuff. By using MMKeyboard hardware @{b}any@{ub} Amiga
@{b}should@{ub} be able to use a reset handler. If you are using the @{"power mode" link "FAQSPICPowerSW"}
then the reset handler is working before power off, too!@{par}

There are a few limits dictated by the handler mechanism:@{par}

There is no way to avoid the reset. Around 10 to 12 seconds after pressing the
reset keys, the system is restarting. This should be enough time to do what is
required.@{par}

It's not possible to use the keyboard during this reset delay phase, because if
the Amiga is answering to the handshake the keyboard is allowed to do a real
reset. If your handler only needs a second and there aren't other programs using
it, then the reset delay is only one second long.@{par}

The handler only gets active when the keyboard was used to reset. An external
reset button or a system crash won't cause the handler to act.@{par}

@endnode

@node "MAST" "MMKeyboard - Main set-up"

@{MS "Main set-up"}

Well, there isn't much to say! Use the cursor keys for selecting and the return
key for entering the @{"hotkey set-up" link "Edit"}. Another way is to press the
hotkey combination to select the right entry. Using the combination again on the
same entry, opens the @{"hotkey set-up" link "Edit"}, too.@{par}

Here're the gadgets of the preferences program:@{par}
@{code}
@{MS "Keyboard set-up"}
@{JCENTER}@{"Keyboard Set-Up" link "KeCh"}
@{"Password set-up" link "Pass"}
@{"PIC set-up" link "PICC"}
@{MS "Hotkey set-up"}
@{JCENTER}@{"Key List" link "MASTLIST"}
@{"New..." link "MASTNEWI"}
@{"Copy..." link "MASTCOPY"}
@{"Edit..." link "MASTEDIT"}
@{"Remove..." link "MASTDELE"}

@{"Save" link "MASTSAVE"}
@{"Use" link "MASTOKOK"}
@{"Cancel" link "MASTCANC"}

---------------------------------------------------------------------------
@{"Main Window" link "MAsT"} @{"Edit Window" link "Edit"} @{"Global Set-Up" link "KeCh"}
@{"Keyboard editor" link "KeEd"} @{"Password set-up" link "Pass"} @{"Password GUI Set-up" link "PaGU"}
@{"PIC Set-up" link "PICC"}

@endnode
@node "MASTKeCh" "Main Set-up - Global Set-Up..."
@toc "MAST"

@{MS "Global Set-Up..."}

This button opens the @{"Global Set-Up" link "KeCh"} window.@{par}

@endnode
@node "MASTPaSe" "Main Set-up - Password Set-up..."
@toc "MAST"

@{MS "Password Set-up..."}

This button opens the @{"password set-up" link "Pass"} window.@{par}

@{b}This gadget isn't available within the Amithlon version!@{ub}@{par}

@endnode
@node "MASTPiSe" "Main Set-up - PIC Set-up..."
@toc "MAST"

@{MS "PIC Set-up..."}

This button opens the @{"PIC set-up" link "PICC"} window.@{par}

@{b}This gadget isn't available within the Amithlon version!@{ub}@{par}

@endnode
@node "MASTLIST" "Main Set-up - The Key List"
@toc "MAST"

@{MS "The Key List"}

This list contains all user defined hotkeys. By pressing return or using the
@{"edit" link "MASTEDIT"} gadget you are able to @{"edit" link "Edit"} the keys.
The @{"new" link "MASTNEWI"} gadget allows to add a new key and the @{"remove" link "MASTDELE"} gadget
allows to delete the active one!

@endnode
@node "MASTNEWI" "Main Set-up - New..."
@toc "MAST"

@{MS "New..."}

Creates a new hotkey and opens the @{"hotkey set-up" link "Edit"} window for the new hotkey.@{par}

@{b}Aborting the @{"hotkey set-up" link "Edit"} window causes the new entry to be removed.@{ub}@{par}

@endnode
@node "MASTCOPY" "Main Set-up - Copy..."
@toc "MAST"

@{MS "Copy..."}

Clones the current hotkey and opens the @{"hotkey set-up" link "Edit"} window for it.@{par}

@{b}Aborting the @{"hotkey set-up" link "Edit"} window causes the new entry to be removed.@{ub}@{par}

@endnode
@node "MASTEDIT" "Main Set-up - Edit..."
@toc "MAST"

@{MS "Edit..."}

By pressing on this button the @{"edit" link "Edit"} window opens and allows you to change the
hotkey settings.

@endnode
@node "MASTDELE" "Main Set-up - Remove..."
@toc "MAST"

@{MS "Remove..."}

After a safety request the selected hotkey will be removed from list!

@endnode
@node "MASTSave" "Main Set-up - Save"
@toc "MAST"

@{MS "Save"}

The settings will be saved into MMKeyboards icon and used as well. The hotkey configuration will be
stored in the ENV: directory. All MMKeyboard windows will close immediately.

@endnode
@node "MASTOkOk" "Main Set-up - Use"
@toc "MAST"

@{MS "Use"}

The window will be closed and the settings used, but the settings won't be saved!

@endnode
@node "MASTCanc" "Main Set-up - Cancel"
@toc "MAST"

@{MS "Cancel"}

This button closes the window and all changed settings are lost!

@endnode

@node "Pass" "MMKeyboard - Password Set-up"
@toc "MAST"

@{MS "Password Set-up"}

@{b}When using Amithlon this window isn't available!@{ub}@{par}

By using this window it's possible to setup the whole password GUI set-up!@{par}

@{b}This window only has a effect on the GUI! The password must be enabled to use the features
within this window. @{"Deactivating the GUI" link "PassActi"} is only disabling the GUI not the
password request itself.@{ub}@{par}

@{code}
@{JCENTER}@{"Password GUI" link "PassGUIP"}
@{"Open on Screen" link "PassScre"}
@{"Password Active" link "PassActi"}
@{"Use" link "PassOkOk"}
@{"Options..." link "PassPaGu"}
@{"Cancel" link "PassCanc"}

---------------------------------------------------------------------------
@{"Main Window" link "MAsT"} @{"Edit Window" link "Edit"} @{"Global Set-Up" link "KeCh"}
@{"Keyboard editor" link "KeEd"} @{"Password set-up" link "Pass"} @{"Password GUI Set-up" link "PaGU"}
@{"PIC Set-up" link "PICC"}

@endnode
@node "PassGUIP" "Password Set-up - Password GUI"
@toc "Pass"

@{MS "Password GUI"}

This gadget allows to specify the GUI for the password session.@{par}

Well, these GUI aren't real programmed GUIs! They just require a picture, an icon and
a few @{"tool type settings" link "PaGU"}.@{par}

@endnode
@node "PassScre" "Password Set-up - Open on Screen"
@toc "Pass"

@{MS "Open on Screen"}

If you want the password requester to open on a separate screen then just turn
this switch on. Otherwise the request opens on the default screen.@{par}

@endnode
@node "PassActi" "Password Set-up - Password GUI Active"
@toc "Pass"

@{MS "Password GUI Active"}

This switch enables the password GUI!@{par}

@{b}Important: The password itself must be disabled by using the @{"PIC set-up" link "PICC"}. It's not possible to deactivate the password without changing the @{"PIC" link "FAQSPIC"}!
The password check is hardware controlled! The Amiga is only getting the cursor position!@{ub}

@endnode
@node "PassOkOk" "Password Set-up - Use"
@toc "PaGU"

@{MS "Use"}

By pressing this button you confirm that the settings within this window are valid.

@endnode
@node "PassPaGu" "Password Set-up - Options..."
@toc "PaGU"

@{MS "Options..."}

This buttons opens the @{"Password GUI Set-up" link "PaGu"} for the selected GUI.

@endnode
@node "PassCanc" "Password Set-up - Cancel"
@toc "PaGU"

@{MS "Cancel"}

Closes the window and restores all settings to their previous values.

@endnode

@node "PaGU" "MMKeyboard - Password GUI Set-up"
@toc "PASS"

@{MS "Password GUI Set-up"}

@{b}This window is not available when using Amithlon!@{ub}@{par}

This window allows to change the configuration of the password gui. There is no need to edit the
tooltypes by hand, because this window is doing this for you.@{par}

@{code}
@{JCENTER}@{"Screen Mode" link "PaGUScre"}
@{"Font" link "PaGUFont"}
@{"Text Position X" link "PaGUEdLe"}
@{"Text Position Y" link "PaGUEdTo"}
@{"Window Position X" link "PaGUWiLe"}
@{"Window Position Y" link "PaGUWiTo"}
@{"Save" link "PaGUSave"}
@{"Test..." link "PaGUTest"}
@{"Cancel" link "PaGUCanc"}

---------------------------------------------------------------------------
@{"Main Window" link "MAsT"} @{"Edit Window" link "Edit"} @{"Global Set-Up" link "KeCh"}
@{"Keyboard editor" link "KeEd"} @{"Password set-up" link "Pass"} @{"Password GUI Set-up" link "PaGU"}
@{"PIC Set-up" link "PICC"}

@endnode
@node "PaGUScre" "Password GUI Set-up - Screen Mode"
@toc "PaGU"

@{MS "Screen Mode"}

The screen mode is used when the @{"'Open on Screen'" link "PassScre"} option is activated.@{par}

If the selected screen mode isn't available on your system, or there isn't enough memory to open the
specified screen, the default screen is used as fall back.@{par}

@{b}Set-up the screen depth to avoid automatic dithering by the datatypes.library.@{ub}

@endnode
@node "PaGUFont" "Password GUI Set-up - Font"
@toc "PaGU"

@{MS "Font"}

This font is used to display the "*" chars during password session.@{par}

@endnode
@node "PaGUEdLe" "Password GUI Set-up - Text Position X"
@toc "PaGU"

@{MS "Text Position X"}

The specified value describes the X position of the password text, depending on the left upper edge
of the password picture.@{par}

@endnode
@node "PaGUEdTo" "Password GUI Set-up - Text Position Y"
@toc "PaGU"

@{MS "Text Position Y"}

The specified value describes the Y position of the password text, depending on the left upper edge
of the password picture.@{par}

@endnode
@node "PaGUWiLe" "Password GUI Set-up - Window Position X"
@toc "PaGU"

@{MS "Window Position X"}

This just describes the window position on screen. A value of zero forces MMKeyboard to centre the
picture in x direction.@{par}

@endnode
@node "PaGUWiTo" "Password GUI Set-up - Window Position Y"
@toc "PaGU"

@{MS "Window Position Y"}

This just describes the window position on screen. A value of zero forces MMKeyboard to centre the
picture in y direction.@{par}

@endnode
@node "PaGUSave" "Password GUI Set-up - Save"
@toc "PaGU"

@{MS "Save"}

Closes the window and stores the password gui set-up within the pictures icon.@{par}

@endnode
@node "PaGUTest" "Password GUI Set-up - Test..."
@toc "PaGU"

@{MS "Test..."}

Opens a fake password window for testing purpose.@{par}

Press "return" or left mouse button on the picture to quit password mode testing.@{par}

@endnode
@node "PaGUCanc" "Password GUI Set-up - Cancel"
@toc "PaGU"

@{MS "Cancel"}

Closes the window and restores all settings to their previous values.

@endnode

@node "Edit" "MMKeyboard - Hotkey Set-up"
@toc "MAST"

@{MS "Hotkey Set-up"}

This window allows to set-up a hotkey.
@{code}
@{MS "Key Set-up"}
@{JCENTER}@{"Name" link "EditName"}
@{"Hotkey" link "EditHoKe"}
@{"Task Name" link "EditTask"}
@{MS "Command Set-up"}
@{JCENTER}@{"Execute Type" link "EditExTy"}
@{"Stack" link "EditStac"}
@{"Command" link "EditComm"}
@{"Current Directory" link "EditCuDi"}
@{"Output File" link "EditOuFi"}
@{"Use" link "EditOkOk"}
